      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Many experts argue that a swift transition to renewables alone might not be fast or reliable enough to meet aggressive net-zero targets without significant energy gaps. Nuclear power is often seen as a necessary \"baseload\" power source that can provide consistent, high-density, carbon-free energy while renewables scale up. Therefore, for many climate models, nuclear is considered a crucial component rather than just an optional add-on for achieving deep emissions cuts.",
